Field Detail

GET_FEATURE

static final String GET_FEATURE
The name of the OGC Web Feature Service (WFS) GetFeature operation. The GetFeature operation returns a selection of features from the WFS data store. GetFeature is valid value for the request parameter.

Used by all versions of WFS.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

OPERATION_PARSING_FAILED

static final String OPERATION_PARSING_FAILED
The name of the OGC Web Feature Service (WFS) OperationNotSupported exception code. Indicates that a request is badly formed and failed to be parsed by the web service. Web service exceptions with this code are typically followed by one or more exception codes that indicate how the request is badly formed.

Used by all versions of WFS.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

OPERATION_PROCESSING_FAILED

static final String OPERATION_PROCESSING_FAILED
The name of the OGC Web Feature Service (WFS) OperationProcessingFailed exception code. Indicates that the web service encountered an error while processing a request. This is typically used to indicate an internal error in the web service.

Used by all versions of WFS.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

RESOURCE_ID

static final String RESOURCE_ID
The name of the OGC Web Feature Service resourceID parameter. The associated value must be a persistent unique resource identifier assigned by the service to a feature. When both the resourceID and typeNames parameters are present in a WFS request, the feature must be of a type specified in typeNames, otherwise the server returns an exception.

Used by WFS version 2.0.0.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

TYPE_NAMES

static final String TYPE_NAMES
The name of the OGC Web Feature Service typeNames parameter. The associated value must be the name of one or more feature types published in a WFS server's Capabilities document. Multiple feature types are delimited by a comma.

Used by WFS version 2.0.0.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

WFS_SERVICE_NAME

static final String WFS_SERVICE_NAME
The abbreviated name for an OGC Web Feature Service (WFS). WFS_SERVICE_NAME is valid value for the service parameter. Used by all versions of WFS.
